<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="SQ8" checkit-title="Absolute convergence">
    <statement>
        <p>
            For each of the following series, determine if the series is <em>convergent</em>, and if the series is  <em>absolutely convergent</em>.
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <m>\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{4 \, {\left(n^{3} + n^{2}\right)} \left(-1\right)^{n}}{n^{7} + 5 \, n^{5}}.</m>
            </li>            
            <li>
                <m>\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{\left(-1\right)^{n + 1}}{n}.</m>
            </li>            
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
       <ol>
            <li>
                
                        <m>\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{4 \, {\left(n^{3} + n^{2}\right)} \left(-1\right)^{n}}{n^{7} + 5 \, n^{5}}</m> converges  and is absolutely convergent.                
                    
                
            </li>            
            <li>
                
                        <m>\displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{\left(-1\right)^{n + 1}}{n}</m> converges but is not absolutely convergent.               
                    
                
            </li>            
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
